reviewText: My mom had this tape and wore it out so she had to buy another one.This is split up into three parts.20 minutes of fat burning aerobics,20 minutes of relaxing stetch,and the 10 minutes of it is a stress reduction sequence as you lay down and close your eyes when jane talks all the stress out of you.This is a great tape to do on days when I am stressed out to the max or having cramping and muscle pains.This tape burns fat with fun easy to follow aerobics.Improve flexibility and makes you feel great with the stretches.The stress reduction is a great way to end the workout.This tape is a must have for people who are beginning an exercise program and who are stressed out.If you like this you will definately like Jane Fonda`s Yoga.
summary: great cardio with great stress reduction

reviewText: This is an all time favorite of mine and I recently ran into a young woman where I work who actually knows who Jane Fonda is AND uses her videos. Jane enlisted talented exercise physiologists to create these videos - they're not the most modern but they are timeless. This particular video is great for people just starting to exercise, getting over an injury or surgery. Once you're feeling better, you can ramp it up with more movement. The exercisers hehind Jane in this video represent the pregnant, the older woman, the token guy : ) and women who can really pour it on. The real reason I ordered this VHS tape was because the other one wore out after about 5 years of frequent use. This particular program is on a DVD with another JF exercise program but that was much more expensive. This will work just fine.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I like 99% of Jane's exercise tapes.  This one is pretty good but not one of her bests.  The stretching feels good.  The aerobics part is pretty good.  At least it is good for a 57 year old women.  Probably not challenging enough if you are younger and more active.There is a relaxation section at the end where you stress and then relax certain body parts.  I have heard this on several audio tapes I have and for some reason I just don't like that approach.  I guess when I am trying to relax I do not want to tense up body parts before I relax them.  I get bored.This is a good tape just not excellent like some of her others.  I wish she would make more recent tapes because the leotards with matching socks are just too old fashion.  Just can't believe we use to wear those outfits but I know I did.  I think I had a dozen colored socks to go with my colored leotards!
Title: N/A
